---
title: Remix
name: Remix
description: Send email from a Remix route action with the top-level mail().
category: Frameworks
---

Postboi is framework-agnostic â€” read the request's `FormData` in a route `action` and hand it
straight to [`mail()`](/api). Postboi extracts the [special fields](/formdata#special-fields)
and renders the rest into a tidy HTML table.

```tsx
// app/routes/_index.tsx
import { Form } from '@remix-run/react';
import { mail } from 'postboi';

export async function action({ request }: { request: Request }) {
	const form = await request.formData();

	// Reply-to comes from the submitted email, so replying reaches the sender.
	form.set('_reply_to', String(form.get('contactâ†’email') ?? ''));
	form.set('_subject', 'Contact Form');

	await mail({ body: form });
	return { ok: true };
}

export default function Index() {
	return (
		<Form method="post" encType="multipart/form-data">
			<input name="contactâ†’name" placeholder="Name" required />
			<input name="contactâ†’email" type="email" placeholder="Email" required />
			<textarea name="detailsâ†’message" placeholder="Message" />
			<button type="submit">Send</button>
		</Form>
	);
}
```

Field names use the [`fieldsetâ†’field`](/formdata#grouped-fields) syntax. The provider and
default recipient come from [`postboi.config.ts`](/config) â€” a `POSTBOI_TOKEN` routes to
[Postboi Cloud](/cloud), or pick any [provider](/providers).

**Runnable example:** [`examples/remix-provider-postboi`](https://github.com/darbymanning/postboi/tree/main/examples/remix-provider-postboi).
